2.A 40% probability that each free neutron will cause a fission<br>
event to occurr is required to make a barely critical mass.<br>
3. .4 * 13 cm = 5.2 cm <br>
4. The density of pure  Pu 239 metal is 19.1 gm per cubic centimeter.<br>
5. If we calculate critical mass for a cube we find that <br>
V= S*S*S<br>
6. 5.2 cm * 2 = 10.4 cm<br>
7. 10.4 * 10.4 * 10.4 = 1125 cubic centimeters<br>
8. 19.1 * 1125 = 21 485 grams = 21.485 kg .<br>
9. 5.2 / 13 = .4 * 100 = 40 %.<br>
10. To make an A-bomb with 100 % pure Pu 239   we <br>
want the atomic core to stay sub critical before<br>
the  core assembly  occurrs.,<br>
11. So lets us make the core 80% of the barely critical mass.<br>
12..This is 17.2 kg of solid plutonium metal.<br>
13. If  If implode this with a uniform implosion wave <br>
and increase the density by a factor of two in the core<br>
we now have .8 * .4 = .32<br>
14. .32  * 2  = .64<br>
15. .64 * 100 = a 64 % probability that each free neutron will cuase a fission event to occurr in the plutonium ball.<br>
16..64 * 2.5 -3 = 1.6 - 1.92 neutrons of all neutrons generated will cause a fission event to occurr and release<br>
2.5 -3 more neutrons per event.<br>
17. This defines a supercritical configuration for a solid ball of plutonium metal.<br>
18. Th result is atomic explosion.<br>
19. This is the secret of the physics of implosion type type A-bombs.<br>
