Plutonium  239 refer to what stage of its radioactive decay <br>
cycle the Plutonium 239 is in* .<br>
2. Reactor grade plutonium contains large amounts of Pu-240<br>
and the plutonium is thus in the alpha phase of its decay<br>
 cycle.<br>
3. After Most up the Pu 240 has decayed via spontaneous fission  the Plutonium 239  has then reached the delta phase<br>
of its decay cycle.<br>
4. After Plutonium 239  has been stored for some time<br>
its Pu -240 content is greatly reduced because <br>
most of the Pu-240 has undergone spontaneous fission<br>
and thus been destroyed by this.<br>
5. In other fields such as chemistry,or crystallograpy Alpha phase  and delta phase my have a different meaning.*<br>
<br>
